# Quiz / Test Builder Tool — Implementation Plan

## Overview

A new standalone tool for the ESL Learning Platform that lets teachers **design custom assessments** with multiple question formats, media support, and advanced settings — then **share those tests** with students via a code or link so they can be taken on any device. Results are collected in real time.

> **Key distinction from Live Quiz:** The Live Quiz is a real-time multiplayer *game* where everyone answers simultaneously and scores are ranked. The Quiz Builder is an *assessment tool* — the teacher creates a test offline, shares it, and students take it independently at their own pace. Think "Google Forms for ESL assessments, but beautiful."

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **This is a large feature.** The plan below is organized in **4 implementation phases** so we can deliver incrementally, get your feedback, and adjust. Please review each section and let me know if you'd like to re-prioritize, remove, or adjust anything before I begin.

> [!WARNING]
> **Media file storage (Feature 2):** Uploaded audio/images need to live somewhere accessible when a student takes a shared test on another device. Options analyzed below — this has cost/complexity implications worth discussing.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Google Sheets integration (Feature 7):** Requires a Google Apps Script web app deployment on your Google account. It's feasible but involves steps outside this codebase. Full analysis below.

---

## Architecture Decisions

### Consistent with existing patterns
- **Standalone HTML page** (`test-builder.html`) + dedicated CSS (`css/test-builder.css`) + JS (`js/test-builder.js`)
- **Separate student-facing HTML page** (`take-test.html`) — a minimal, isolated page students access via shared link. **No navigation to other tools** (no header, no tools link, no back button to dashboard).
- **Firebase Realtime Database** — reuses the existing [firebase-service.js](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Documents/esl-learning-platform/js/firebase-service.js) config for test sharing & real-time result collection
- **Google Drive** — reuses [GoogleDriveService](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Documents/esl-learning-platform/js/google-drive-service.js#17-397) for teacher save/load of quiz templates
- **CSS custom properties** — follows existing theming (`--indigo-velvet`, `--medium-slate-blue`, etc.) + dark mode via `body.dark-mode`
- **No build system** — pure vanilla HTML/CSS/JS, consistent with the rest of the platform

### New patterns introduced
- **Test data model** — a JSON schema for the test definition stored in localStorage, Google Drive, and Firebase
- **Student-facing isolated page** — `take-test.html` will be a self-contained page with no access to the rest of the platform
- **Google Apps Script webhook** — for pushing results to Google Sheets (optional, can be added later)

