### Phase 3: Test Sharing & Student Taking

---

#### [NEW] [take-test.html](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Documents/esl-learning-platform/take-test.html)

An **isolated, student-facing page** with:

- **No header, no navigation, no links to other tools** — students see only the test
- A clean, beautiful, animated test interface
- Student identification form (name + **course group dropdown** with default options: 3A, 3B, 3C, 4A, 4B, 4C, 5A, 5B, 5C, 5D)
- **Full-screen anti-cheating mode** — page enters fullscreen when the test begins
- Question-by-question navigation with progress bar
- Timer display (if time limit set)
- **Timing data capture** — records start time, end time, and duration
- Results screen at the end

---

#### Full-Screen Anti-Cheating Mode

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **How it works:** When a student clicks "Start Test" on the identification screen, the page requests fullscreen via the Fullscreen API (`document.documentElement.requestFullscreen()`). While the test is active:
>
> - If the student **exits fullscreen** (presses Escape or uses browser controls), the `fullscreenchange` event fires and a warning overlay appears
> - If the student **switches to a different tab**, the `visibilitychange` event detects `document.hidden === true` and logs the incident
> - Each violation is logged with its type (`tab-switch` or `fullscreen-exit`) and timestamp
> - The total violation count is included in the student's response data sent to Firebase
> - The teacher sees the violation count on the response dashboard (Phase 4)
>
> **Graceful degradation:** If the browser doesn't support Fullscreen API (rare) or the user denies the prompt, the test still works — violations are simply not tracked.

---

#### Test Timing Data Collection

> [!NOTE]
> Each student response automatically records:
> - `startedAt` — timestamp when the student clicks "Start Test"
> - `completedAt` — timestamp when the student submits the final answer
> - `durationSeconds` — calculated elapsed time
>
> These appear in the teacher's response dashboard and CSV export (Phase 4).

