---

#### Sharing Mechanism

**How it works:**

1. Teacher clicks **"Share Test"** in the builder
2. The system:
   - Generates a 6-character alphanumeric code (like the Live Quiz)
   - Uploads the full test JSON to Firebase under `tests/{CODE}`
   - Sets an expiration timestamp (e.g., 7 days by default, configurable)
3. Teacher gets:
   - The **code** to share verbally in class
   - A **direct URL**: `https://yoursite.com/take-test.html?code=ABCDEF`
   - A **QR code** (generated client-side) students can scan
4. Students:
   - Visit `take-test.html` and enter the code, OR
   - Open the direct link / scan QR
   - Enter name and select course group → take the test

> [!NOTE]
> The URL will be relative to wherever this platform is hosted. If you deploy via GitHub Pages or Firebase Hosting, the link will be a full URL. For local dev, it'll be `http://localhost:8080/take-test.html?code=ABCDEF`.

**Security considerations:**
- Tests are **public by read** on Firebase (anyone with the code can take it) — this is intentional for ease of sharing
- The code is unguessable (6 chars from `ABCDEFGHJKLMNPQRSTUVWXYZ23456789` = ~887 million combinations)
- Teacher can **deactivate** a shared test to stop new submissions
- Firebase security rules should allow read of `tests/{code}` and write to `tests/{code}/responses/{responseId}` — but NOT allow modifying the test itself
- **Full-screen mode** adds an extra layer of academic integrity monitoring

