### Phase 4: Real-Time Response Collection

---

#### Response Collection Strategy

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Two complementary approaches recommended:**

**Approach A — Firebase RTDB (built-in, real-time):**
- Student responses are written to `tests/{code}/responses/{responseId}` in Firebase
- Teacher can view responses in real time from the builder page (a "Responses" tab)
- Responses include: student name, **course group**, answers, score, **start time, duration, and violation count**
- Teacher can export responses as CSV from the builder

**Approach B — Google Sheets (optional add-on):**

| Aspect | Details |
|---|---|
| **How** | A Google Apps Script deployed as a web app receives POST requests with response data |
| **Setup** | Teacher creates a Google Sheet → deploys a small Apps Script → pastes the webhook URL into the builder settings |
| **Data sent** | Student name, group, each answer, score, **start time, duration, violation count** |
| **Limitation** | Requires the teacher to set up a Google Apps Script (one-time), which involves ~5 steps outside this codebase |

**My recommendation:** Implement Firebase-based collection first (Approach A) — it's fully within our control and works immediately. Add the Google Sheets webhook as an optional "advanced" feature with clear setup instructions.

---

#### Response Dashboard (in test-builder.html)

A "Responses" tab in the builder that shows:
- Live response counter
- Student name, **course group**, score, **start time, duration**
- **Violation count per student** (with color coding: 0 = green, 1-2 = yellow, 3+ = red)
- Per-question breakdown (% correct per question)
- Export to CSV button (includes all timing and violation data)

