## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification (per phase)

**Phase 1 — Builder UI:**
1. Start the local dev server with `node server.js`
2. Open `http://127.0.0.1:8080/tools.html` and verify the new "Quiz Builder" card appears
3. Click the card and verify the builder page loads
4. Create a test with at least one question of each type (MC, T/F, fill-blank, matching, unjumble words, unjumble letters, drag-drop)
5. Verify live preview renders correctly for each type
6. Save to localStorage and reload — verify the test persists
7. Test dark mode toggle

**Phase 2 — Media & Settings:**
1. Upload an image to a multiple-choice question and verify it displays in the editor preview
2. Upload an audio file and verify playback works in the editor
3. Toggle multi-select for MC and verify behavior changes
4. Toggle word bank for fill-in-the-blank
5. Save a media-heavy test to Google Drive and reload it

**Phase 3 — Sharing & Taking:**
1. Create a test and click "Share"
2. Copy the share code and open `take-test.html?code=XXXXXX` in a separate browser / incognito
3. Enter student name and group → take the test → verify results screen
4. Verify the student page has NO navigation to other tools
5. Test on a mobile device (or mobile emulation) for responsive design
6. Verify timer works if time limit is set

**Phase 4 — Response Collection:**
1. Have 2-3 students (or incognito tabs) take a shared test
2. Verify responses appear in real-time on the teacher's response dashboard
3. Export responses as CSV and verify data correctness
4. Test Google Sheets webhook (if configured)

### Browser Testing
- I will use the Playwright browser tool to verify page rendering, navigation, and core interactions after each phase.
